<div id="review_7324324" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/7324324" />
    <a title="adam" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/34450-adam"><img alt="adam" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/7324324?book_show_action=true">Oct 05, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="adam" class="user" itemprop="url" name="adam" href="/user/show/34450-adam">adam</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer7324324" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5758730372877648340">Standard 19th century French novel? Not even close. This book defies almost every convention of the novel, and it was written before any of those conventions were even recognized! No hero, no heroine, no real plot; no morality lesson; Machiavellian politics for everyone; love doesn&apos;t conquer all; love doesn&apos;t even exist in this world until the main character gets locked away in prison for a womb-like nine months; a narrator who couldn&apos;t care less about the whole thing...this is so modern it hurt</span>
  <span id="freeText5758730372877648340" style="display:none">Standard 19th century French novel? Not even close. This book defies almost every convention of the novel, and it was written before any of those conventions were even recognized! No hero, no heroine, no real plot; no morality lesson; Machiavellian politics for everyone; love doesn't conquer all; love doesn't even exist in this world until the main character gets locked away in prison for a womb-like nine months; a narrator who couldn't care less about the whole thing...this is so modern it hurts. I wouldn't call this an easy or fun read, but I find myself thinking about the book a lot, long after I've finished it. It's really difficult to place and kinda powerful because of it...</span>
  <a data-text-id="5758730372877648340" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


