<div id="review_3882643433" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3882643433" />
    <a title="Luís" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/117399210-lu-s"><img alt="Luís" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1620236159p2/117399210.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3882643433?book_show_action=true">May 20, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Luís" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Luís" href="/user/show/117399210-lu-s">Luís</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9789727081820" href="/book/show/32454742-a-cartuxa-de-parma">review of another edition</a>


          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Luís by: </span>
      <a href="/user/show/45926752-jes-s-de-la-jara">Jesús De la Jara</a>
  </div>


          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/117399210-lu-s?shelf=2021-readings">2021-readings</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/117399210-lu-s?shelf=france-belgium-swiss">france-belgium-swiss</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/117399210-lu-s?shelf=romance">romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/117399210-lu-s?shelf=classics">classics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/117399210-lu-s?shelf=recommendations">recommendations</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/117399210-lu-s?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3882643433" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2752068100867850184">A criticism of Stendhal is a bit like undertaking a vertiginous ascent without equipment; beware of slippery ground! The Charterhouse of Parma, in this case, is one of those monuments of French literature that readers share. It has marked many generations of high school students with varying degrees of happiness, leaving everyone with mixed impressions ranging, under the responsibility of more or less inspired teachers, from rejection to passion. Let us recall the facts: on September 3, 1838, St</span>
  <span id="freeText2752068100867850184" style="display:none">A criticism of Stendhal is a bit like undertaking a vertiginous ascent without equipment; beware of slippery ground! The Charterhouse of Parma, in this case, is one of those monuments of French literature that readers share. It has marked many generations of high school students with varying degrees of happiness, leaving everyone with mixed impressions ranging, under the responsibility of more or less inspired teachers, from rejection to passion. Let us recall the facts: on September 3, 1838, Stendhal had the idea of ​​writing the Charterhouse of Parma. On November 4, Stendhal moved to 4 Rue Caumartin in Paris. For seven weeks, he set to work and dictated the text of the Charterhouse to a secretary. On December 26, he gave his editor a text of more than five hundred pages. This bulimia of work requires, in itself, respect. And so there appears the extravagant hero of Stendhal, whose story we could briefly summarize: Fabrice del Dongo leads a peaceful and happy life with his family on the shores of Lake Como. But the young man dreams of glory on the battlefields and goes to fight with Napoleon Bonaparte in Waterloo, bad pick regarding the choice of the battle, which will cause him many problems with the political authorities. Wanted, suspected of espionage, he hiding by his aunt. It is then that he meets the beautiful Clélia whose beauty subjugates him.<br />An epic novel, The Charterhouse of Parma, did not meet with resounding success when it was released. Balzac's support would be necessary for this story to finally break out of a desire to live that was both joyous and tragic. In 19th century Italy, the reality of history rises to the fabulous, to adventure, borders on the romantic. It is all the talent of Stendhal to sublimate its events. In a story where he speaks to us of heroism, through the feelings of revenge, incest, tyrannicide, the naivety of a dreamy hero overwhelmed by the world around him.<br />To conclude, a pleasant novel that traces a bygone era where it is challenging to project oneself, dating a little, refers to many other stories of the nineteenth century but do not have the power to evoke Hugo or Zola.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2752068100867850184" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

