        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3690795556" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9407479047005385654">An entertaining, eventful, humorous, romance novel about Fabrice del Dongo, a young Italian aristocrat. Fabrice as a 17 year old, is headstrong and decides to go and fight in France with Napoleon. The time is after Napoleon’s Russian retreat. By chance he ends up on a battlefield at Waterloo, not really knowing what he was doing other than that for a time he was riding with Generals. When he arrives back in Italy he is provoked and kills a man. Fabrice is arrested. Fabrice is a man of principles</span>
  <span id="freeText9407479047005385654" style="display:none">An entertaining, eventful, humorous, romance novel about Fabrice del Dongo, a young Italian aristocrat. Fabrice as a 17 year old, is headstrong and decides to go and fight in France with Napoleon. The time is after Napoleon’s Russian retreat. By chance he ends up on a battlefield at Waterloo, not really knowing what he was doing other than that for a time he was riding with Generals. When he arrives back in Italy he is provoked and kills a man. Fabrice is arrested. Fabrice is a man of principles and quite proud. His fortune is that he always seems to have lots of money. A rich powerful middle aged woman falls in love with him, but Fabrice falls in love with a beautiful young woman whilst he is in prison. There are complications!<br /><br />An enjoyable read. First published in French in 1839.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9407479047005385654" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
